 ### Nucleus Configuration
 
-- Platform Override only supports `architecture.detail`, please refer known
-  issues link
-  [here](https://github.com/aws-greengrass/aws-greengrass-lite/issues).
+- Platform Override supports `architecture.detail` for both the cloud
+  `resolveComponentCandidates` request and **local manifest matching**. When a
+  recipe manifest includes `"architecture.detail"` in its `Platform` section,
+  Nucleus Lite compares it against the device's
+  `platformOverride.architecture.detail` from `config.yaml`. This allows
+  differentiating boards that share the same CPU architecture (e.g. two
+  different aarch64 boards). Manifests without `architecture.detail` act as
+  wildcards and match any device.
